RICH KIVEL: What were
some of the learnings?

00:09:53.114 --> 00:09:57.050
It sounds like you modified
the business model throughout.

00:09:57.050 --> 00:10:00.986
There were learnings
[INAUDIBLE] You integrated

00:10:00.986 --> 00:10:02.462
different approaches.

00:10:02.462 --> 00:10:05.831
What were some of the learnings
that came out of that?

00:10:05.831 --> 00:10:07.330
What would you have
done differently

00:10:07.330 --> 00:10:10.730
if you were
relaunching it today?

00:10:10.730 --> 00:10:12.117
PROFESSOR: Rich, is your mic on?

00:10:12.117 --> 00:10:12.700
BOB JONES: OK.

00:10:12.700 --> 00:10:15.150
Rich's question,
for those of you

00:10:15.150 --> 00:10:17.620
who may not have heard it
from the back of the room,

00:10:17.620 --> 00:10:20.210
was what were some of
my learnings so far?

00:10:20.210 --> 00:10:23.010
And if I were to relaunch the
business today, what would

00:10:23.010 --> 00:10:25.390
I do differently?

00:10:25.390 --> 00:10:36.460
And I think that most
entrepreneurs are stubborn.

00:10:36.460 --> 00:10:37.996
I'm no exception to that.

00:10:44.090 --> 00:10:49.360
Well, you almost
never tackle something

00:10:49.360 --> 00:10:51.730
that's going to be easy.

00:10:51.730 --> 00:10:56.180
And I have a guy on my
business advisory board

00:10:56.180 --> 00:11:02.810
who will give me 10 reasons why
every idea I have will fail,

00:11:02.810 --> 00:11:05.790
and why every suggestion
I make is dumb.

00:11:05.790 --> 00:11:09.000
And it's quite useful because
eight of the 10 things

00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:11.370
he'll rattle off, I've
thought about and addressed.

00:11:11.370 --> 00:11:14.730
And two of them I think, ooh,
I'd better think about that.

00:11:14.730 --> 00:11:17.740
But you have to be willing
to walk through walls

00:11:17.740 --> 00:11:19.110
because it's hard.

00:11:19.110 --> 00:11:21.950
And most of you will fail.

00:11:21.950 --> 00:11:24.200
I did.

00:11:24.200 --> 00:11:26.505
You'll just need to
decide that as a jockey,

00:11:26.505 --> 00:11:28.840
you need a different horse.

00:11:28.840 --> 00:11:32.490
But I found something
that worked.

00:11:32.490 --> 00:11:34.460
And I went out and
proudly talked about it

00:11:34.460 --> 00:11:36.450
to the investment community.

00:11:36.450 --> 00:11:38.130
And then I tried it.

00:11:38.130 --> 00:11:39.270
And I tried it.

00:11:39.270 --> 00:11:40.900
And I tried it.

00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:42.410
And it didn't work.

00:11:42.410 --> 00:11:44.720
So one of the things I
would have done differently,

00:11:44.720 --> 00:11:47.370
were I to do it
again, would have

00:11:47.370 --> 00:11:50.910
been to test the idea
right from the get-go,

00:11:50.910 --> 00:11:53.600
rather than just assuming
that because it had worked

00:11:53.600 --> 00:11:56.840
in the past, that this market
and this group of people

00:11:56.840 --> 00:12:00.084
was like the last market and
the last group of people.

00:12:00.084 --> 00:12:01.084
PROFESSOR: That's great.

00:12:07.390 --> 00:12:08.960
BOB JONES: Yes sir.

00:12:08.960 --> 00:12:11.001
AUDIENCE: It seems like
most of it is [INAUDIBLE]

00:12:25.314 --> 00:12:27.230
BOB JONES: I don't really
